<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f97466416012740>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=1&mid=97466416012740>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=1&mid=97466416012740>RE: 18 warrior, wonderin where to fight now</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=1&mid=97466416012740#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Nov 19th 3:02 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2303><span id=Scholar>roytheodd</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>18 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've just slugged my way into level 20 and can tell you that the hunting sites aren't too bountiful. While I've listed nine, only the first two allow you so grind through a level quickly. The others merely provide the fun in EQ by mixing things up and letting you see the world. Depends on what you want out of the game I guess. I have ordered the list in order of recommendation, with number one being most recommended. (I've changed my mind about this... see last paragraph)<br><br>1) Croc hunting in Oasis of Marr is good, even though you're bored of it.<br> <br>2) Highpass Hold is also good exp and really good loot but it can be hard to get into a group and you frequently have to put your name on waiting lists just to get into a group. There are two really good spots to fight in HH and these are the orc and gnoll spawns--a few named occasionally appear and drop quality magic items. If you're an evil race then you'll have to accept the fact that you can only kill orcs until your faction rises. Best of all is that you can be bound here... no long corpse run here.<br><br>3) Gorge of King Xorbb has some baddies in it that are good to kill. You'll probably want to have a healer with you here because it's sort of remote and you never know what kind of pain lies around the corner. Watch out for evil eyes and don't trust what they con to you--they're harder than that. This zone has a few crummy magic items on the common spawns and some nice ones on the high level camps. If you're evil the nearest bind point is HH and it's a long run through the Karana Canyon to get back here--so don't die in the Gorge. Oh, this zone is also known as the Minotaur Gorge and the Beholder's Maze.<br><br>4) Lake Rathetear is a neatly divided zone and there are plenty of things to slay here. Just enter the zone and ask what camp you can join and you should do quite well. Get into Aviak groups as soon as possible because they'll give the best exp for the longest number of levels in this zone. This place is far from any banks so weight management becomes a factor in game play... kinda fun. You can be bound one zone over in the Arena.<br><br>5) The Timorous Deep is a good place to fight if you have a cleric with you. If you take the raft from the Oasis of Marr you will land at an island with an ogre village. I have heard stories of people gaining up to four levels in a day by fighting these guys, mind you it was a cleric and warrior team, not a whole group and not solo. Also, if you're an evil race, killing these ogres will seriouly tweak your Kunark faction and will make it so you can't be bound in Kunark. I don't know if this is true for good races though. I personally have never fought the ogres, but the stories I've heard regarding the experience they give make me recommend fighting them.<br><br>6) Lavastorm Mountains can offer up some exp for you. I killed here intermittently on my climb from 17 to 19. I don't like the randomness of spawns, even though that's closer to what EQ wants than camping. In an open zone like this I just didn't find exp to pile up very quickly and the landscape, while neat, doesn't spur me to fight here much.<br><br>7) KUNARK can offer up lots of challenges and you'll really be seeing the world. I can't help too much with hunting grounds here because I've only traveled here with a troll. I know where a level 18 troll can fight, but not any of the good races. A level 18 troll can fight along the beaches of The Overthere, or in the Warsliks Woods. Just be warned that The Overthere is a high level zone (15-40) and that level 18 is still on the low side... have a SoW at all times to flee the tombstone aggros.<br><br>8) You can try camping the castle in Crushbone. Evil races should avoid this because with every kill in Crushbone you lose faction with Neriak and Nektulous groups. On the bright side though, you can get some good magic items here, spawns are fast and vicious, and you'll get to be the guy starting trains instead of only being wailed on by someone else's mess.<br><br>9) Befallen has a few things you can kill, but you'll want a cleric with you here. The cleric's ability to handle undead will be vital in here, as well as their healing skills. The key system in place can make it a pain in the neck to retrieve a corpse if you're soloing on the lower levels, so use caution if you solo. At level 18 you'll need to delve down to the lower levels to get exp too.<br><br>10) Najena is right off of Lavastorm Mountains. At level 18 you're still on the low end of the level range and you might have a bit of fun if you get in a good group, but they're hard to form at your level inside the dungeon... form one in Lavastorm and then come in here. Personally, I didn't like Najena while still in the teen levels, but maybe that's just me.<br><br><br>Palooka, level 22 troll warrior, Quellious server<br><br><br>Edited:<br>After picking up two levels in two days soloing I have changed my mind about the best place to hunt... I would definitely vote for The Overthere if you're an evil race. The zone is set up so that if you stay along the north shore you'll be in the lower level part of the zone. Almost nothing aggroed on me ever, the exception being when two Sarnak Conscripts just happened by at the same time and figured they could take me (they couldn't). If you stay near the cliff golem you can run to him when you're in real danger and he'll slay things for you. There is a bank and merchants in the zone and you can be bound here too. It's basically like a newbie zone for level 15-25 warriors. As a troll with a big experience penalty I can see the exp bar move visibly with each kill near my level. Loot is good--sabertooth fangs and rhino horns selling for nearly a plat with a charisma of 36. The area is still unused on Quellious server--I've seen exactly five other people hunt there over the course of the twelve or so hours I was there, and they were all dark elf enchanters or necromancers. If you can get a cleric to travel with you you'll be a killing machine. One word of advice though, DON'T KILL THE OGRES IN TIMOROUS DEEP despite what I said in #5 on the above list. Killing them makes it very difficult to get to Kunark for evil races and I'm told that it hurts your Kunark faction so that you can't be bound there.<br><br>I've left The Overthere at level 22 in search of the next new thing... I'm bored with Southern Karana before I'm even there... If any of you have advice on where I should be please post it here... I prefer Kunark. Thanks.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
